cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about image restoration using deep neural networks. The main focus is on incorporating non-local operations into a recurrent neural network for image restoration. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new design for the recurrent neural network, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on image denoising and super-resolution, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
